<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-635-639  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 635 639.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Nov 26 1990 v7 n48 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DEC offerings help banks construct branch networks; firm offersnew software, consulting services. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Digital Equipment Corp is introducing DECbank-Branch, a newsoftware that helps banks build branch office networks.andP;  Theproduct lets banks build platform automation networks that letbank personnel electronically open new accounts and mergeinformation from different data bases to answer customerquestions.andP;  Users can also use microcomputer- or server-basedapplications to design custom savings and loan programs.andO;DECbank-Branch runs on VMS-based VAXes.andP;  The product can beaccessed by directly attached terminals or microcomputers runningclient software.andP;  The package includes a variety of applicationprogram interfaces (APIs) that allow the VAX to support DEC aswell as other vendor banking applications.andP;  DEC is hopingDECbank-Branch will convince bankers to install DEC VAXes onm branch office Ethernets as servers.andP;  This would provide file andapplication sharing services to local terminals andmicrocomputers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DEC.andO;Product:   DECbank-Branch (Banking/finance/investment software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     BankingSoftware PackagesApplications Programming InterfaceBranch BankingLocal Area NetworksOffice AutomationFinancial Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>